AB  - The focus of academic libraries has always on providing access to reliable information and indigenous scholarship via a website. In this regards, this paper aimed to explore the current status of the contents and features of academic library websites in Pakistan. Library Websites of 39 universities were studied by adopting a checklist procedures. The results of selected academic library websites' features and contents clearly show that the recent situation of these websites is not up to the mark and some have undeveloped web pages that do not guide the users much about the library services, resources, staff and library policies. In addition, majority of the library websites were missing imperative features like; updated contents, staff profile, users' account information, site map, help, geographical map and photo gallery services. Overall, very few library websites have been struggling to bridge the digital divide and represent the country academic and research profile. Some suggestions are presented, which can further develop the status of university library websites in Pakistan as well as in other developing countries. [ABSTRACT FROM AUTHOR]
